<font color="#FF0000">REGRET</font><br>
<tt>Tue May 20  2:39:25 US/Eastern 1997
</tt><p>
I served 365 Days 6 hrs and 20 min in Viet Nam, from June 68 till June 69. I was stationed in Phan Rang for 6 months, Da nang 5 months, and na Trang 1 month with a few days in Saigon.<br>
I flew missons into Quang Tree, Ben hoi, and numerous other little places during my tour.  We flew in steaks, ice creame, addn ammo : and bodies out. We sprayed agent orange ande dropped anti personell bombs.<br>
We drank beer after duty and played vollyball and ate pilfered steaks.  Got attacted by rockets, snipers, and mortars almost every day and night. My two next door neighbors I grew up with were killed one week apart while I was smoking marijuana in a comforable quanset hut.<br>
I saw an F4 pilot killed 50 yards from me when his fuel tank exploded on landing. I saw Da Nang practally blown up by our own men letting an out of control brush fire get into the army andy marine bomb dump. 24 hrs of 500 lbs bombs flattened our barracks.<br>
I spent every night I could at the NCO club getting drunk. I was arrested once for fighting.<br>
All in all, the biggest impression on me was the fact that people who claimed to be religious<br>
were killing each other on both sides.<br>
After I got out I searched for a religion that didn't belive<br>
in killing their fellow man. I found it!! <br>
I am now one of Jehovah's witnesses. Gog will soon do away with war and those who cause it forever,<br>
and make the wearth a paradise. For more information on this Email me. I just wish I had known<br>
what I know now because I would have gone to prison rather than go into the military during the Viet nam era.
